1 SENATE FLOOR VERSION
February 24, 2026
2
3 SENATE BILL NO. 1327 By: Jech of the Senate
4 and
5 Newton of the House
6
7
8 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Tourism and
Recreation Department; amending 74 O.S. 2021,
9 Sections 2203, 2204, and 2206, which relate to the
Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Commission;
10 transferring certain duties to the Commission;
modifying powers and duties of the Executive
11 Director; requiring certain oath; establishing
organizational and meeting requirements for the
12 Commission; authorizing the Commission to appoint
Executive Director; providing for determination of
13 salary; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 2203, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 2203. A. The Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation
20 Commission shall be an advisory body to the Executive Director of
21 the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department and shall consist of
22 eight (8) members who shall serve a term of six (6) years.
23 Effective January 14, 2019, all duties and powers of the Commission
24 shall be transferred to the Executive Director. Any provision in
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1327 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 stat ute that provides to the Commission authority that is not
2 advisory in nature shall be deemed to grant the duty or power to the
3 Executive Director. No more than one Commission member shall be
4 from any one county. The Lieutenant Governor shall serve as an ex
5 officio voting member of the Commission.
6 B. One member shall be appointed from each congressional
7 district, who shall be a resident and a qualified elector in the
8 district from which appointed, and the remaining members shall be
9 appointed from the state at large. If congressional districts are
10 redrawn each member appointed shall complete the current term of
11 office at which time a new appointment shall be made in compliance
12 with the redrawn congressional district.
13 C. Commission members shall be appointed by the Governor, with
14 the advice and consent of the Senate, and shall serve at the
15 pleasure of the Governor. Whenever a vacancy on the Commission
16 occurs by death, resignation, or otherwise, the Governor shall fill
17 the same by appointment, with the advice and consent of the Senate,
18 and the appointee shall hold office during the unexpired term. Each
19 member shall hold office until a successor has been appointed and
20 qualified. Five members of the Commission shall constitute a
21 quorum, and the vote of the majority of members present shall be
22 necessary for any action to be taken by the Commission. No vacancy
23 in the membership of the Commission shall impair the rights of a
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1327 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 quor um to exercise and perform all the rights and duties of the
2 Commission.
3 D. With the exception of the ex officio, no member of the
4 Commission shall seek election to a federal, state, or county office
5 while serving on the Commission.
6 E. Each member of the Commission, before serving on the
7 Commission, shall take and subscribe to the constitutional and
8 statutory oaths of office and file the oaths with the Secretary of
9 State. Members of the Commission shall be reimbursed for travel
10 expenses to Commission meetings as provided in the State Travel
11 Reimbursement Act.
12 F. The Commission shall be organized by the Governor who shall
13 appoint from the Commission the chair, the vice chair, and the
14 secretary. The Commission shall adopt rules pursuant to the
15 provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act to execute the
16 powers and duties of the Commission and the Oklahoma Tourism and
17 Recreation Department.
18 G. The Commission may meet monthly and shall meet at least
19 quarterly. The Commission may meet at such other times as it deems
20 necessary for effectively performing its duties and
21 responsibilities. Special meetings may be called by the chair or by
22 any three members of the Commission. The meetings of the Commission
23 shall be subject to the Oklahoma Open Meeting Act.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1327 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 H. The Commission is hereby declared to be a governmental
2 agency and instrumentality of this state with authority to exercise,
3 in addition to those it now has, the rights, privileges, and
4 functions specified.
5 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 2204, is
6 amended to read as follows:
7 Section 2204. There are hereby granted to and imposed in the
8 Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Commission, and in any commission or
9 body which may succeed to the powers, rights, and duties of the
10 Commission, Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department the following
11 additional powers, rights, and duties:
12 1. Sue and be sued;
13 2. Adopt, use, and alter an official seal;
14 3. Make bylaws for the management and regulation of its
15 affairs;
16 4. Appoint, prescribe the duties, and fix the compensation for
17 officers, agents, and employees;
18 5. Make contracts and execute instruments as in the judgment of
19 the Department Commission are necessary or convenient to the
20 exercise of the powers conferred upon it by law; and
21 6. Promulgate rules and policies necessary and convenient to
22 the exercise of the powers conferred upon it by law.
23 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 2206, is
24 amended to read as follows:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1327 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Section 2206. The chief executive officer of the Oklahoma
2 Tourism and Recreation Department shall be the Executive Director,
3 who shall be appointed by the Governor, with the advice and consent
4 of the Senate, Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Commission, and who
5 shall serve at the pleasure of the Governor Commission and may be
6 removed or replaced without cause. The Executive Director shall be
7 chosen with regard to knowledge, training, experience, and ability
8 to administer the functions of the Department. Compensation for The
9 Commission shall establish the salary of the Executive Director
10 shall be determined pursuant to Section 3601.2 of this title.
11 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
12 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT, WORKFORCE
AND TOURISM
